The paper discusses the effectiveness of vocabulary mappings for information retrieval, which is a key topic in the field of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also mentions the use of controlled vocabularies (thesauri, classification systems, subject heading lists), which are commonly used in Digital Libraries (cs.DL) and Natural Language Processing (cs.CL). The evaluation of the vocabulary mappings in an information system environment also suggests a focus on Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Databases (cs.DB).
